The former Imo State governor, Owelle Rochas Okorocha on Monday has pleaded not guilty to the N2.9 billion corruption charges brought against him by the Federal Government. Okorocha who appeared before a Federal High Court in Abuja is facing and accused of diverting N2.9 billion from Imo State government House Accounts and Imo State Local Government Joint accounts to private companies. However, the former governor denied all the 17-count charges against him. -Advertisement- The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) counsel, Gbolahan Latona, pleaded with Justice Inyang Ekwo for an adjournment to enable him to arrange and present his 15 witnesses. Justice Ekwo ruled that he would take all the bail applications on May 31 and ordered Okorochaâ€™s further detention till May 31 when his bail application would be argued.